SIMPLE: mezzotint
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mezzotint
<hw>Mez"zo*tint</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>mezzo-tinto</ets>.]</ety> <def>A manner of engraving on copper or
steel by drawing upon a surface previously roughened, and then removing
the roughness in places by scraping, burnishing, etc., so as to produce
the requisite light and shade. Also, an engraving so produced.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mezzotint</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Mezzotint
<hw>Mez"zo*tint</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To engrave in
mezzotint.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mezzotinter</ent>⟦br⟧
